#: ../../variables/variables_advanced.rst:84
msgid "Track Relationship Variables"
msgstr "Variabelen van nummerrelaties"

#: ../../variables/variables_advanced.rst:86
msgid ""
"If you enable tagging with :doc:`Use track relationships <../config/"
"options_metadata>`, you get these extra variables:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../variables/variables_advanced.rst:88
msgid "**_lyricistsort**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../variables/variables_advanced.rst:90
msgid "The sort names of the lyricists for the work. (*since Picard 2.9*)"
msgstr ""
"De sorteernamen van de tekstschrijvers van de compositie. (*Sinds Picard "
"2.9.*)"

#: ../../variables/variables_advanced.rst:92
msgid "**_performance_attributes**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../variables/variables_advanced.rst:94
msgid ""
"List of performance attributes for the work (e.g.: \"live\", \"cover\", "
"\"medley\"). Use :ref:`func_inmulti` to check for a specific type (i.e.: "
"``$if($inmulti(%_performance_attributes%,medley), (Medley),)``). (*since "
"Picard 1.3*)"
msgstr ""
"Een lijst met eigenschappen van de compositie (zoals ‘live’, ‘cover’ of ‘"
"medley’). Je kan :ref:`func_inmulti` gebruiken om te kijken of een "
"specifieke eigenschap van toepassing is (bijv. ``$if($inmulti"
"(%_performance_attributes%,medley), (Medley),)``). (*Sinds Picard 1.3.*)"

